sequenceDiagram
    actor Client

    participant API as BloggingSystem.Api<br/>(MediatR Pipeline)
    participant AuthHandler as CreateAuthorCommandHandler
    participant PostHandler as CreatePostCommandHandler
    participant QueryHandler as GetPostByIdQueryHandler
    participant ES as IEventStore<br/>(InMemory / Marten)
    participant AuthorsDB as authors schema<br/>(PostgreSQL)
    participant RabbitMQ as RabbitMQ
    participant Consumer as AuthorCreatedConsumer<br/>(Posts.Infrastructure)
    participant PostsDB as posts schema<br/>(PostgreSQL)
    participant OutboxProc as OutboxProcessor<br/>(BackgroundService)

    %% ─── Phase 1: Create Author ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    Note over Client,PostsDB: Phase 1 — POST /author  (seeds KnownAuthors via RabbitMQ)

    Client->>API: POST /author<br/>{"name":"Alice","surname":"Smith"}<br/>Authorization: Bearer <token>
    API->>API: ValidationBehavior — validate fields
    API->>AuthHandler: CreateAuthorCommand
    AuthHandler->>AuthHandler: Author.Create() → raises AuthorCreatedEvent
    AuthHandler->>ES: AppendEventsAsync(authorId, [AuthorCreatedEvent])
    AuthHandler->>AuthorsDB: AuthorProjection.ProjectAsync()<br/>UPSERT authors.Authors
    AuthHandler->>RabbitMQ: IIntegrationEventPublisher.PublishAsync(AuthorCreatedEvent)<br/>(via MassTransit)
    API-->>Client: 201 Created {"id":"<authorId>"}

    RabbitMQ-->>Consumer: consume AuthorCreatedEvent
    Consumer->>PostsDB: UPSERT posts.KnownAuthors<br/>(authorId, name, surname)

    %% ─── Phase 2: Create Post ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Note over Client,PostsDB: Phase 2 — POST /post  (event sourcing + outbox)

    Client->>API: POST /post<br/>{authorId, title, description, content}<br/>Authorization: Bearer <token><br/>X-Idempotency-Key: req-abc-123
    API->>API: IdempotencyBehavior — check posts.ProcessedCommands<br/>(key not found → proceed)
    API->>API: ValidationBehavior — validate fields
    API->>PostHandler: CreatePostCommand
    PostHandler->>PostsDB: KnownAuthorRepository.GetByIdAsync(authorId)<br/>SELECT posts.KnownAuthors ✓
    PostHandler->>PostHandler: Post.Create() → raises PostCreatedEvent
    PostHandler->>ES: AppendEventsAsync(postId, [PostCreatedEvent])
    PostHandler->>PostsDB: OutboxWriter.WriteAsync([PostCreatedEvent])<br/>INSERT posts.OutboxEvents (ProcessedAt = NULL)
    PostHandler->>PostsDB: PostProjection.ProjectAsync()<br/>UPSERT posts.Posts (read model)
    API->>PostsDB: IdempotencyBehavior — INSERT posts.ProcessedCommands<br/>(key, serialized result)
    API-->>Client: 201 Created {"id":"<postId>"}

    %% ─── Phase 2b: OutboxProcessor (crash recovery) ──────────────────────────
    Note over OutboxProc,PostsDB: Phase 2b — OutboxProcessor polls every 5 s (crash recovery only)

    loop every 5 seconds
        OutboxProc->>PostsDB: SELECT posts.OutboxEvents WHERE ProcessedAt IS NULL
        alt pending entries found (e.g. crash between write and project)
            OutboxProc->>PostsDB: PostProjection.ProjectAsync() — re-project events
            OutboxProc->>PostsDB: UPDATE OutboxEvents SET ProcessedAt = now
        end
    end

    %% ─── Phase 3: Query Post ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Note over Client,PostsDB: Phase 3 — GET /post/{id}  (read model query)

    Client->>API: GET /post/<postId>?includeAuthor=true
    API->>QueryHandler: GetPostByIdQuery(postId, includeAuthor=true)
    QueryHandler->>PostsDB: PostReadRepository.GetByIdAsync(postId)<br/>SELECT posts.Posts (denormalised, includes AuthorName)
    PostsDB-->>QueryHandler: PostReadModel
    QueryHandler-->>API: PostDto {id, title, content, author:{name, surname}}
    API-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>{id, authorId, title, description, content,<br/> author:{id, name, surname}}
